President Emmerson Mnangagwa triggered South African whites to ask the US President to impose sanctions. This was in November, 3 weeks before Donald Trump abruptly disconnected South Africa over alleged racially motivated abuse of whites.

Mnangagwa made a proclamation over how easy it is to chase white farmers, triggering angers. Video:

@POTUSyou must bring back the sanctions to Zimbabwe. They haven't learned to behave
